2)NON-PRIMITIVE
A non-primitive data type is a data type that can store multiple values or more complex data. Unlike primitive data types, they are not simple single-value types.
nonprimitive data types are SET,DICTIONARY,SEQUNECE

ðŸ“Œ CHARACTERISTIC
Can hold multiple values
Can be ordered or unordered
May allow modification (mutable) or not (immutable)
Built on top of primitive types
Often referred to as reference types

